definition: to succeed/to finish/to complete/to accomplish/to become/to turn into/to be all right/OK!/one tenth
to have achieved nothing/to be a total failure/to get nowhere

sentences.english: The school board members spend their time disputing and getting nothing done.
sentences.chinese: 學校董事們爭論不休，但一事無成。

sentences.english: Hell, in the past few years you’ve been all but killed about a million times.
sentences.chinese: 該死，在過去的幾年裏你除了虛度光陰以外一事無成。

sentences.english: As happened in that boom, most of these ideas will come to naught.
sentences.chinese: 就像那次熱潮一樣，這些思想大都一事無成。

sentences.english: If you don't concentrate on your work, you can accomplish nothing.
sentences.chinese: 如果你不把心思放在工作上，你終將一事無成。

sentences.english: If we fail to grasp the opportunity, we would have lifelong Cengdeng, nothing.
sentences.chinese: 要是不能把握機會，就要終身蹭蹬，一事無成。

sentences.english: Without it, nothing could ever be brought to a conclusion; everything would be in state of chaos.
sentences.chinese: 不準時將一事無成，事事都會陷入混亂不堪的境地。

sentences.english: If you lack willpower, you can achieve nothing.
sentences.chinese: 如果你缺乏意志，你永遠將一事無成。

sentences.english: If you don't work hard, you'll finish up nowhere.
sentences.chinese: 如果你不勤奮，最終將一事無成。

sentences.english: People can't do something themselves, they wanna tell you you can't do it.
sentences.chinese: 那些一事無成的的人想告訴你你也成不了大器。

sentences.english: People can't do some itself then they want to tell you , you can't do it.
sentences.chinese: 那些一事無成的人想告訴你也成不了大器。

sentences.english: He will never achieve anything if he doesn't work.
sentences.chinese: 如果他不付出勞動，將永遠一事無成。

sentences.english: He procrastinated until it was too late to do anything.
sentences.chinese: 他拖延耽誤以致一事無成。

sentences.english: Without the help of parents, the Song Zheng also may accomplish nothing.
sentences.chinese: 如果沒有學生家長的幫助，宋鄭還可能會一事無成。

sentences.english: I have no secret of success but hard work.
sentences.chinese: 除辛苦農做之外，人別無成過的竅門。

sentences.english: If you don't concentrate your mind on work, you will finally achive nothing.
sentences.chinese: 如果你不把心思放在工作上，你終將一事無成。

sentences.english: People cyour't do something themselves-they would - tell you you cyour't do it.
sentences.chinese: 那些一事無成的人想通告你你也成不了大器。
